transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Hello, how we doing, sir?

Speaker 2: Hello, can you hear me?

Speaker 1: Yes, Mr. Coleman?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: In El Paso, Texas?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Yeah, how may I assist you, sir? I see you have a prescription for Viagra, 50 milligrams.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: How can I help you, sir?

Speaker 2: I need to cancel that prescription.

Speaker 1: Any health concern, or are you just trying to order as needed?

Speaker 2: Say what?

Speaker 1: I said, any health concern, or are you just trying to order as needed?

Speaker 2: Uh, there's no health concern. Um, I'm not...

Speaker 1: Or you just want to order as needed?

Speaker 2: Say what?

Speaker 1: You just want to order as needed, meaning that you don't want to get the refill, but you just want to call in?

Speaker 2: Say that one more time?

Speaker 1: I said, you just want to order as needed? Uh, like pausing the prescription, so you just call to order, so they don't send you no refill at the moment? You have a lot left?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I have a whole bunch left. I got like three bottles left, but me and my wife is not, not doing it like that.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, yeah. No, I can tell the pharmacy to cancel the initial writing from the physician.

Speaker 2: And, because you're not active, obviously, they're going to pause the prescription, so that way when you reorder, you don't pay a more expensive price, because they're going to save the prescription, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: They're probably asking up to half a year, and you can reorder, so you're not on a monthly anymore, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So, let me do that for you.

Speaker 1: All right. And, give us a call to reorder, or press your quick refill button, okay? I'm advising the pharmacy to pause the prescription for now, because you have a lot left, okay?

Speaker 2: Yes. And, could you send me a confirmation email saying that you paused the prescription?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: You will receive that tomorrow. Our email service is closed for the day, because we're closing right now, literally one minute. But, you will receive an email tomorrow, okay? I'm going to place a request for that.

Speaker 1: Okay, I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: You're welcome. Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: All right. Bye.
